t necessarily a strong anomaly.\n\n### Hypothesis Formulation:\n\nGiven the scenario and the data, we can propose hypotheses around communication or performance bottlenecks within critical services:\n\n#### Hypothesis 1:\n- **Component**: `cartservice` pods\n  - **Reason**: Dramatic increase in `rrt_max` and `rrt` suggests synchronous or resource-intensive operations are causing delays.\n  - **Evidence**: High `rrt_max` of up to 1.6M during fault indicates potential service degradation due to backend issues or contention.\n\n#### Hypothesis 2:\n- **Component**: `frontend` pods \n  - **Reason**: Elevated `rrt` and `rrt_max` across pods imply elevated request-processing delays.\n  - **Evidence**: Consistency in increased latency metrics across all pods in service indicates a potential cross-service communication bottleneck.\n\n### JSON Output Format:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"NEUTRAL\",\n  \"detected_metric_keys\": [\"client_error_ratio\", \"error_ratio\", \"rrt_max\", \"rrt\", \"pod_cpu_usage\"],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"cartservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"High rrt_max values indicate potential communication or processing bottlenecks.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Fault period rrt_max values exceed 1.6M compared to normal median of ~8K.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"frontend\",\n      \"reason\": \"Consistent high latency in rrt and rrt_max indicates performance issues across service interactions.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Rrt_max increased from ~270K to over 1.6M consistently across all pods.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nNext steps involve deeper inspection of service interdependencies or misconfigurations that might be giving rise to these symptoms.", "current_hypothesis": "frontend is the root cause due to severe processing delays in CartService operations, as indicated by trace and metric anomalies."}
